result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason Duncan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jason Duncan is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jason Duncan was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Jason Duncan was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

[MK] case called at 10:31am 
Defendant Jason Duncan in court, in custody.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Mr. Duncan confirms that he continues to wish to proceed without counsel at this hearing.
Troop A. Polizzi- sworn & testifies
--direct examination by ADA Shock
--cross examination by Mr. Duncan
Argument is given by ADA Shock.
The Court dismisses Count #1 without prejudice. The Court indicates the State may bring the charge if the State can show that Mr. Duncan acted without the authorization of victim and he had knowlege that he was acting without such authorization.
The Court reviews Bond due to the dismissal of the felony charge.  Argument is given by ADA Shock
The Court modifies the Cash Bond amount to now be a $2,000 Cash Bond with the same conditions as previously ordered.  
The Court preserves Defendants rights and schedules the case for status conference in August so that further time is given for the Public Defender to appoint counsel.
